"Lai C.-C.A., Dietrich D.E., Bowman M.J.","Global warming and the mining of oceanic methane hydrate",2005,"Topics in Catalysis","32","3-4",,"95","99",,,10.1007/s11244-005-2879-4,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-18244380610&partnerID=40&md5=cb4bb5b44c36b1b2309b789f5683b289","Earth/Environmental Sci. Division, Los Alamos National Laboratory, Los Alamos, NM, United States; AcuSea, Inc., Albuquerque, NM, United States; Marine Sciences Research Center, State University of New York, Stony Brook, NY, United States","Lai, C.-C.A., Earth/Environmental Sci. Division, Los Alamos National Laboratory, Los Alamos, NM, United States; Dietrich, D.E., AcuSea, Inc., Albuquerque, NM, United States; Bowman, M.J., Marine Sciences Research Center, State University of New York, Stony Brook, NY, United States","A discussion on the earth's carbon budget and the associated energy transfer between various components of the climate change covers the biochemical processes which slowly interact with geophysical processes in climate system; a hypothesis that internal processes in the oceans rather than in the atmosphere are at the center of global warming; chemical energy stored in biochemical processes that can significantly affect ocean dynamics; a new hypothesis for global warming, which is caused by the enhanced atmospheric greenhouse (warming) effect due to increased concentrations of greenhouse gases, e.g., water vapor, CO2, CH4, N2O, and CFC; and a revolutionary strategy to deal with global climate change.","Carbon dioxide; Global warming; Greenhouse gases; Heat content; Methane; Methane bubbles; Methane hydrate; Methane oxidation; Ocean warming",,,,,,,"United Nations Environmental Programme: Introduction to Climate Change, , http://www.grida.no/climate/vital/11.htm; (2001) IPCC Third Assessment Report - Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis, p. 874. , (Cambridge University Press); U.S. Department of Energy: All About Hydrates, , http://www.netl.doe.gov/scng/hydrate/